&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Squishable is a close-knit team of designers, artists, pop culture-fanatics, and lovers of all things adorable. Together we create the cutest, cuddliest, (and sometimes downright unusual) plush and lifestyle products in the world. With the millions-strong Squishable fan community cheering us on (and a lot of cupcakes, coffee, and karaoke) we make people say &quot;awww.&quot; Our offices are in a sunny Soho loft in NYC, and downtown Washington DC.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;The Director of Wholesale Sales is responsible for managing and growing Squishable’s wholesale sales channel. Their concentration will be on creating and executing a strategic plan for growing existing accounts as well as finding, securing, and growing new accounts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expanding Squishable’s core business lines while developing and executing strategies to support the new product line launches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing and developing the internal sales team, which consists of six to eight sales professionals who handle house account sales, trade show operations, and national and key account management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building Squishable&#39;s inside sales strategy, including developing outreach programs, training sales staff, and determining incentive programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing and training Squishable’s independent sales representative teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing and growing the existing domestic customer base by building specialty, national, and mid-tier retailers, catalog, and buying group relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing 10-15 national and international trade shows annually, including attending and representing the company at high-profile shows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Soliciting feedback and implementing suggestions from Squishable’s most important wholesale customers through semi-annual meetings of our retailer boards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Growing Squishable’s European subsidiary by:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with the executive team to formulate and execute our European growth strategy;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recruiting and training independent European sales representative teams or distributors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinating with the production and sourcing team to determine the optimal product selection for the European market&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Growing Squishable’s international market share by working with existing international distributors outside of Europe and generating leads for new distributors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working directly with customers in our custom/white-label production business&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working in tandem with the product development team to develop new lines and product concepts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties as assigned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wholesale sales experience with specialty toys/gifts is required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CRM/ERP—Comfortable with using CRM systems to manage leads and existing customer relationships. Experience with NetSuite is a plus, but not a requirement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reporting—Experience building actionable reports and presenting KPIs and recommendations to the executive team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Microsoft Office Suite—Intermediate Excel and Word&lt;/li&gt;
